{
  "local_port": 43438,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I apply driving license in Bangalore?",
  "response": "To apply for a driving license in Bangalore, follow these steps:\n\n### Step 1: Enroll in a Driving School\nEnroll in a recognized driving school in Bangalore to learn the rules and regulations of driving. After completing the course, you will receive a training completion certificate.\n\n### Step 2: Fill Out the Application Form\nYou can apply for a driving license online through the official website of the Ministry of Road Transport and Highways, which is [Parivahan](https://parivahan.gov.in/). Follow these steps:\n\n1. Visit the Parivahan website.\n2. Click on \"Driving Licence Related Services\".\n3. Select \"Karnataka\" from the dropdown menu.\n4. Choose \"Apply for Learner Licence\".\n5. Fill out the application form with your personal details and the type of vehicle you wish to obtain a license for.\n\n### Step 3: Upload Required Documents\nYou will need to upload scanned copies of the following documents:\n\n- Age proof (e.g., birth certificate, passport, etc.)\n- Address proof (e.g., Aadhar card, voter ID, utility bill, etc.)\n- Training completion certificate from the driving school (if applicable)\n\n### Step 4: Pay the Application Fee\nPay the required fee online. The fee amount may vary depending on the type of license you are applying for.\n\n### Step 5: Book a Slot for the Learner's License Test\nAfter submitting your application and paying the fee, book a slot for the learner's license test. You will be required to take a written test on traffic rules and regulations.\n\n### Step 6: Appear for the Learner's License Test\nVisit the designated Regional Transport Office (RTO) on the scheduled date and time to take the learner's license test. If you pass the test, you will receive your learner's license.\n\n### Step 7: Practice Driving\nWith your learner's license, you can start practicing driving. Make sure you are accompanied by a person with a valid permanent driving license.\n\n### Step 8: Apply for Permanent Driving License\nAfter 30 days (but within 180 days) of receiving your learner's license, you can apply for a permanent driving license through the Parivahan website. Follow these steps:\n\n1. Visit the Parivahan website.\n2. Click on \"Driving Licence Related Services\".\n3. Select \"Karnataka\" from the dropdown menu.\n4. Choose \"Apply for Driving Licence\".\n5. Fill out the application form and upload the required documents (learner's license, age proof, address proof).\n\n### Step 9: Pay the Application Fee\nPay the required fee for the permanent driving license online.\n\n### Step 10: Book a Slot for the Driving Test\nBook a slot for the driving test at the designated RTO.\n\n### Step 11: Appear for the Driving Test\nVisit the RTO on the scheduled date and time for the driving test. If you pass the test, your permanent driving license will be issued.\n\n### Step 12: Receive Your Driving License\nOnce your application is processed and approved, you will receive your permanent driving license either by post or you can collect it from the RTO.\n\n### Important Contacts:\n- **RTO Bangalore Central**: No.15, 2nd Floor, TTMC Building, BMTC, Shantinagar, Bangalore - 560027\n- **RTO Bangalore West**: No.9/8, Sub-registrar Office Building, Behind BDA, Hoshalli, Bangalore - 560091\n- **RTO Bangalore East**: No.17, Basement, TTMC Building, Old Madras Road, Indiranagar, Bangalore - 560038\n\nMake sure to check the specific requirements and any updates on the official Parivahan website before applying.",
